## **What to look for in a Company**

**Sourcing:** 

- [Step-By-Step Guide On How To Find The Right Startups To Invest In](https://about.crunchbase.com/blog/how-to-find-startups-to-invest-in/)
- [4 Major Paths Of Deal Flow](https://www.datadriveninvestor.com/2019/11/03/how-do-vcs-find-and-fund-your-startup-4-major-paths-of-deal-flow/#)
- [Sourcing deals and conducting diligence](https://www.affinity.co/blog/vc-deal-sourcing)

 
Other ways VCs source startups are: 

- Startup accelerator demo days
- Angel.Co
- Product Hunt
- Angel Capital Association

**Readings on metrics:** 

- [**3 Mathematical Models for Building a More Valuable Company:**](https://www.codingvc.com/three-mathematical-models-for-building-a-more-valuable-company/) This post describes three possible models for calculating a startup’s value and the lessons that each model offers.
- [**Total Addressable Market → Serviceable and Obtainable Market**](https://prestonwillisblog.wordpress.com/2015/06/03/understanding-and-using-tam-sam-and-som/)
- [**16 Startup Metrics:](https://a16z.com/2015/08/21/16-metrics/)** A list of the most common or confusing metrics investors focus on.


Finalize the list of 10 startups and select 3 metrics that you think are most important when sourcing companies. 
